    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can check this way where 'HAS' - Returns true if this object has a mapping for name. The mapping may be NULL.</p>\n\n<pre><code>if (json.has(\"status\")) {\n   String status = json.getString(\"status\"));\n}\n\nif (json.has(\"club\")) {\n   String club = json.getString(\"club\"));\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>You can also check using 'isNull' - Returns true if this object has no\n  mapping for name or if it has a mapping whose value is NULL.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<pre><code>if (!json.isNull(\"club\"))\n    String club = json.getString(\"club\"));\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
