    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can use <code>has</code></p>\n\n<pre><code>public boolean has(String key)\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Determine if the <strong><a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/org/json/JSONObject.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">JSONObject</a></strong> contains a <strong><em>specific key</em></strong>.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Example</strong></p>\n\n<pre><code>JSONObject JsonObj = new JSONObject(Your_API_STRING); //JSONObject is an unordered collection of name/value pairs\n\nif (JsonObj.has(\"address\")) { \n    //Checking address Key Present or not\n    String get_address = JsonObj .getString(\"address\"); // Present Key\n}\nelse {\n    //Do Your Staff\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
