    "body" : "<p>I am just adding another thing, In case you just want to check whether anything is created in JSONObject or not you can use <strong>length</strong>(), because by default when JSONObject is initialized and no key is inserted, it just has empty braces <code>{}</code> and using <strong>has</strong>(String key) doesn't make any sense.</p>\n\n<p>So you can directly write <code>if (jsonObject.length() &gt; 0)</code> and do your things.</p>\n\n<p>Happy learning!</p>\n"
  }, {
