    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Json has a method called <code>containsKey()</code>. </p>\n\n<p>You can use it to check if a certain key is contained in the Json set. </p>\n\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>File jsonInputFile = new File(\"jsonFile.json\"); \nInputStream is = new FileInputStream(jsonInputFile);\nJsonReader reader = Json.createReader(is);\nJsonObject frameObj = reader.readObject();\nreader.close();\n\nif frameObj.containsKey(\"person\") {\n      //Do stuff\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
